post_text:
Graduation update: Our tentative plan is that we will be holding our 2020 graduation ceremony on May 22nd at 6:00 at our football field. This ceremony will be open only to our 2020 graduates and their immediate family. We will have the ceremony simulcast along with virtual graduation to be posted later.

We ask that the graduates begin arriving at 5:30 with their immediate family in one vehicle and they will be directed to their appropriate spot. A letter will be sent home later this week with more details.

post_text:
As many of you know, we lost one of our own last week. Brad Lehmkuhl was a big part of what made working at Sebeka great. He was kind, funny, willing to help, never complained and would take time to listen. Everyone who worked with him, could not help but laugh or smile when Brad was around.

We will miss his smile, his laugh, his kindness to everyone he met, trying to find him by listening for his music (the halls at night will be a lot quieter), his stories, his jokes, and of course the Lifesavers and mints,

We all have our memories of Brad but he has made a lasting impression on Sebeka School and anyone who interacted with him. Brad, we will never forget you. Brad is irreplaceable and will be greatly missed by students and staff at Sebeka School. Our hearts go out to Colleen, TJ, Barb and his grandsons.

Kaylie Westberg has been selected for membership in the Minnesota Band Directors Association (MBDA) 6-8 Grade State Honor Band for the 2019-2020 school year. Kaylie was one of 89 students selected from 260 who auditioned this winter for a position in this group.
Kaylie will have the opportunity to work with some of the finest music educators in the state as their section coaches, and will be conducted by Verlene Stotts, Band Director at Discovery Middle School in Fargo, ND. Kaylie and the rest of the band will rehearse with Ms. Stotts on Saturday, April 18th at Marshall High School in Marshall, MN, and will then perform a concert at 2:00 PM on Sunday, April 19th at the Schwann‚Äôs Performing Arts Center at Marshall High School.
Way to go, Kaylie! #sebekatrojans

Spelling Bee
The public is invited to attend the annual Sebeka School Spelling Bee. The Spelling Bee will take place at 8:45 a.m. on Thursday, February 20th, in the gym of Sebeka School. Please enter through door 10 by the main office. There will be two divisions of the Spelling Bee: a Junior Division consisting of third and fourth graders, and the official Sebeka School Spelling Bee consisting of the fifth, sixth, seventh, and eighth graders. The champion of the School Spelling Bee will go on to compete at Sourcewell in Staples on March 25th, 2020.
